e Southern and Appalachian regions of the United States. Some have argued that a-prefixing has its root as a transformation of grammatical constructs such as %0a%3c %0a%3c 'hee set before his eyes king Henrie the eight with all his Lordes ON HUNTING in his forrest at Windsore'%0a%3c %0a%3c losing the 'n' sound over time, leaving a vowel sound behind.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c Sources:%0a%3c %0a%3c Matyiku, Sabina. 2011. A-prefixing. Yale Grammatical Diversity Project: English in North America. (Available online at http://ygdp.yale.edu/phenomena/a-prefixing. Accessed on 2021-04-10). Updated by Tom McCoy (2015) and Katie Martin (2018).%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: A:)%0a%3c (:Category: MorphosyntacticDiversity:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
